man /usr/share/man/man3/mlx_new_window.1
man /usr/share/man/man3/mlx_pixel_put.1

search for how colors are stored in graphic memory
- always: include <mlx.h> and call mlx_init() to start / if it fails it returns NULL
- when compiling add: -lmlx -framework -OpenGL -framework AppKit -L /usr/local/lib

+ mlx_new_window: (manage window)
    + mlx_clear_window
    + mlx_destroy_window

+ mlx_pixel_put : (draw inside window)
    + mlx_pixel_put
    + mlx_string_put
  
+ mlx_new_image : manipulate images
+ mlx_loop : handle keyboard or mouse events / I guess it render to page to the window


